"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-what-next-sydney-mclaughlin-levrone-olympics-2024-gold-medal-400m-hurdles-world-record-b1175623.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  \\\"Ah come on, steady.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Can we not just celebrate thisOlympics?\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not chatting about the next one.\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 343, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport's a classic for this.\\\"\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The words there of Duncan Scott, one of the star's of Britain's swim team, when asked last week within minutes of the end of his third Games whether there might be a fourth.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9913273362707572, \"rank\": 0.004373974849644039, \"text\": \"Duncan Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 428, \"end\": 435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7911848118987783, \"rank\": 0.2639271591419402, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You doubt he is alone in being frustrated by the speed at which the wheel turns and the narrative moves on.\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But whenSydney McLaughlin-Levrone does what she did last night, how can you help but ask: what now?\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the second Olympics in a row, the American broke her own 400m hurdles world record to win gold, a time of 50.37seconds rated by World Athletics's complex points system as the greatest female track performance of all-time.\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999604892772, \"rank\": 2.361415196525112e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 890, \"end\": 905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9996546109300292, \"rank\": 0.00034550840462850666, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On a night when Noah Lyles's bid to emulate Usain Bolt's Beijing, London and Rio sprint doubles fell flat, here was a timely reminder that it is his quieter team-mate who, in pure talent terms, is the closest athletics has seen to the Jamaican great.\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The algorithm, incidentally, still has Bolt's records out ahead: McLaughlin-Levrone's run last night was worth 1,322 of World Athletics's performance points, compared to 1356 (100m) and 1352 (200m) for Bolt's best.\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1357, \"end\": 1372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9996546109300292, \"rank\": 0.00034550840462850666, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, thankfully, McLaughlin-Levrone's greatness will not be measured by spreadsheet when her career ends.\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Given she turned 25 only on Wednesday, there is still plenty of it left.\", \"from\": 1558, \"to\": 1630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The challenge closest to home from here would be to break the 50-second barrier in her specialist event, a ludicrous thought since Anna Cockrell became only the fourth woman to break 52 when claiming silver last night.\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1763, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Cockrell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Cockrell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Winter escapes and activities to end the year in style  McLaughlin-Levrone's coach, Bobby Kersee, though, thinks she can do it, and so seemingly does she.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 2208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1983, \"end\": 1999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 2138, \"end\": 2150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Kersee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Kersee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Kersee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Kersee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was hoping it'd be a little faster, but I am sure there are some things in the middle there we can clean up,\\\" the Texan said last night.\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is always more work to do.\\\"\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her event could yet get harder.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lord Sebastian Coe, the chief of World Athletics, has been talking about raising the height of the hurdles, which are currently six inches lower than in the men's race.\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lord Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}, {\"begin\": 2451, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9996546109300292, \"rank\": 0.00034550840462850666, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That might slow McLaughlin-Levrone down, but it might also exacerbate the gap between her and the rest.\", \"from\": 2587, \"to\": 2690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, what about further afield?\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McLaughlin-Levrone's time last night would have been ninth among the flat 400m semi-finalists on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year, she took a break from hurdles to put genuine focus on that event, running 48.74sec at US Trials, within a whisker of the American record.\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 2980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2929, \"end\": 2938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.9999999933070285, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\"}, {\"begin\": 2964, \"end\": 2972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999604892772, \"rank\": 2.361415196525112e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was due to run the flat lap at the World Championships in Budapest, and would have gone in as favourite, but pulled out with a knee injury, before reverting to her \\\"first love\\\" in Olympic year.\", \"from\": 2981, \"to\": 3178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3043, \"end\": 3051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 0.9231385573098526, \"rank\": 0.08326100354207898, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next year's World Championships in Tokyo offer another window for experiment; Marita Koch's world-record 47.60, set in 1985, another long-range target to shoot at.\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3215, \"end\": 3220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9811354910200955, \"rank\": 0.01922722083739362, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Could she run both?\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The workload would be heavy and, unlike Bol, McLaughlin-Levrone thrives on racing only sparsely.\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3461, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rounds over hurdles in particular, though, would be a doddle, and such is her status now that if she wants to double-up, organisers would surely do all they could to make the schedule work.\", \"from\": 3462, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, fatigue might be the difference between breaking the world record again or not come the final.\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it would be worth it to leave with two individual golds.\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3817, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has even been whispered that she could take on the 800m, where another ancient world record will soon come under threat, perhaps byKeely Hodgkinson.\", \"from\": 3819, \"to\": 3970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3959, \"end\": 3969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.9998696544613638, \"rank\": 0.00013036253077746717, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is a very different event, but on the question of whether McLaughlin-Levrone has the capacity, Kersee ought to be to be a good judge, having coached Athing Mu to Tokyo's gold.\", \"from\": 3971, \"to\": 4151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4125, \"end\": 4134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athing_Mu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athing Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athing_Mu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athing_Mu\"}, {\"begin\": 4138, \"end\": 4143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9811354910200955, \"rank\": 0.01922722083739362, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watching the now double Olympic champion charge off the final hurdle last night, you got the feeling she could do whatever she wants.\", \"from\": 4153, \"to\": 4286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Sa